newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia Oct palm oil output seen little changed.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia Oct palm oil output seen little changed.

text.p: Malaysia's palm oil output in October is estimated to be little changed from September, plantation houses said on Wednesday.
Plantation houses said October output was estimated to have been flat to two percent higher.
"Production has more or less peaked in September, and October output should be about the same," a local plantation house trader said.
He said production should start declining in November.
Malaysian private crop forecaster Ivan Wong, who is expected to release his final crop estimates for October on Thursday, had earlier put October production at 880,000 tonnes, up 1.8 percent.
Official Palm Oil Registration and Licensing Authority (PORLA) figures are due on Friday.
Traders estimated palm oil stocks at the end of October at 950,000-980,000 tonnes compared with PORLA's figure of 894,030 at end-September.
Exports in October were estimated at 700,000-720,000 tonnes against PORLA's 637,079 tonnes in September.
